==Statistics==
===Funding===
The station received a total budget of €11.3 million for 2015.{{cn|date=January 2018}}

===Audience===
According to the 2011 [[Joint National Listenership Research|JNLR]] survey, RnaG has a weekly listenership of 100,000 which equates to a 3% market share.

This is similar to Welsh-language [[BBC Radio Cymru]], which has 116,000 listeners and a 2.4% share.<ref>https://static.rasset.ie/documents/about/18280-rte-languagescheme-bilingual-eng-v4-screen.pdf</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-wales-33794230|title=BBC Cymru Wales loses listeners|first=Huw|last=Thomas|date=6 August 2015|publisher=|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref>

